## Google Sheets CRM Development Rules

### Code Structure Requirements
Every function must follow this structure:
```javascript
function functionName(parameters) {
  console.log('Function started:', parameters);
  
  try {
    // Input validation
    if (!validateInput(parameters)) {
      throw new Error('Invalid input provided');
    }
    
    // Main logic
    const result = processLogic(parameters);
    console.log('Processing complete:', result);
    
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Function failed:', error);
    SpreadsheetApp.getUi().alert('Error: ' + error.message);
    throw error;
  }
}

Data Handling Standards
Only use columns specified in sayfa_kolonlari.md
Validate all dropdown values against allowed options
Use SpreadsheetApp.getUi() for all user dialogs
Log all data transformations with console.log
Handle empty/null values gracefully
UI Development Rules
Create modal dialogs with proper form validation
Pre-fill fields from selected row data
Implement default values (80-90% pre-filled)
Show clear error messages to users
Test all UI interactions before delivery
Testing Requirements
Before saying "code is ready":

 Function executes without errors
 Console shows expected output
 Data saves to correct sheet and columns
 UI opens and closes properly
 All form fields work correctly
 Data validation prevents invalid entries
 Error handling shows user-friendly messages
Synchronization Rules
Sync between Temsilci and Yönetici files
Use employee codes: [Initials]_[Number] (e.g., LG_001)
Maintain data consistency across all sheets
Log all sync operations with timestamps
